Dayo Ojerinde The Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife, Nigeria, has perfected plans to confer honorary doctorate degrees on four eminent Africans. A statement by the Public Relations Officer of the university, Mr Abiodun Olarewaju, listed the awardees as the Rwandan President, Paul Kagame; Marketing Communications guru, Mr Biodun Shobajo; the President of African Export-Import Bank, Dr Benedict Oramah and the Managing Director and Chief Executive Officer of the First Bank of Nigeria Plc, Mrs Ibukun Awosika. It added that they were being honoured for their contributions to the socio-economic and political development of their countries, continent and the world at large. Olarewaju in the statement further explained that the university would confer the Doctor of Sciences D.Sc. (Agric. Economics) (Honoris Causa) on Dr Ben Oramah in recognition of his outstanding academic achievements and unique contributions to finance and trade in Africa. “In the same vein, Mrs Ibukun Awosika’s indelible corporate achievements, unique and outstanding contributions to the growth of entrepreneurship in society, in addition to her humane social activism, earned her the recognition of the university with the conferment of the Doctor of Business Administration (D.BM) (Honoris Causa). “The four honorary awardees will be conferred with their degrees as part of the events marking the 44th convocation of the University holding from Wednesday 11th to Saturday 4th December, 2019,” Olarewaju said. Copyright PUNCH.
